WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.168 --> 00:00:02.570
<i>Previously on</i> Will Trent <i>.</i>

2
00:00:02.704 --> 00:00:04.071
Are you going
to Caleb's tonight?

3
00:00:04.204 --> 00:00:06.073
I don't know.
His family is loud.

4
00:00:06.206 --> 00:00:09.243
Did you know sharks
don't have any bones?
They only have cartilage.

5
00:00:09.376 --> 00:00:11.411
Really?

6
00:00:13.146 --> 00:00:14.816
James Ulster
has a big head start.

7
00:00:14.949 --> 00:00:17.084
<i>We know that Ulster</i>
<i>is well-connected and charming.</i>

8
00:00:17.217 --> 00:00:19.386
It's possible that he's
using people to help him.
and we want to know who.

9
00:00:19.521 --> 00:00:21.488
Now. Ulster's had two fiancées.

10
00:00:21.623 --> 00:00:24.224
-That two-timing--
-Asshole.

11
00:00:24.358 --> 00:00:25.960
Is it possible
that there's a third?

12
00:00:26.093 --> 00:00:30.732
This man dictated my whole life
from the moment I was born.

13
00:00:30.865 --> 00:00:32.000
I have to end this.

14
00:00:32.132 --> 00:00:33.233
What happened?

15
00:00:33.367 --> 00:00:35.302
Ulster took him
from his day camp.

16
00:00:35.435 --> 00:00:37.505
<i>and then. according to Calvin.</i>
<i>Uncle Will traded</i>
<i>places with him.</i>

17
00:00:39.908 --> 00:00:40.842
Time to die.

18
00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:48.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

19
00:01:10.270 --> 00:01:11.839
What do you have for me?

20
00:01:12.205 --> 00:01:15.043
Arson investigators said
there was a lot of
accelerant in the vehicle.

21
00:01:15.175 --> 00:01:17.612
All signs point
to murder-suicide.

22
00:01:17.979 --> 00:01:19.847
Hey. Pete. Just say it.

23
00:01:19.981 --> 00:01:23.718
I can't make
an official determination
yet. but both bodies are male.

24
00:01:24.318 --> 00:01:25.887
Initial assessments
are consistent

25
00:01:26.020 --> 00:01:29.857
with what we expect
for James Ulster
and Special Agent Trent.

26
00:01:31.059 --> 00:01:33.093
We'll work as fast as possible.

27
00:01:45.073 --> 00:01:46.306
I wanna see.

28
00:01:57.986 --> 00:02:00.320
Angie. we're still
processing the scene.

29
00:02:00.454 --> 00:02:01.889
Pete. let her.

30
00:02:09.196 --> 00:02:10.832
Something fused to his chest.

31
00:02:13.835 --> 00:02:14.902
What is this?

32
00:02:17.137 --> 00:02:18.372
Is that a...

33
00:02:19.339 --> 00:02:20.608
a flip phone?

34
00:02:24.444 --> 00:02:25.747
It's not Will's.

35
00:02:26.279 --> 00:02:27.882
He hasn't used
this in over a year.

36
00:02:28.016 --> 00:02:32.053
Pete. Will wears
a gold medallion.
his mother's necklace.

37
00:02:32.185 --> 00:02:33.420
Did you find anything?

38
00:02:33.554 --> 00:02:34.889
We didn't find any jewelry.

39
00:02:35.023 --> 00:02:36.456
-You sure?
-Yeah.

40
00:02:37.190 --> 00:02:39.226
It's not him. It's not Will.

41
00:02:39.359 --> 00:02:41.129
The other body's not gonna be
Ulster either.

42
00:02:41.261 --> 00:02:42.730
This was staged.

43
00:02:42.864 --> 00:02:44.565
Ulster was trying
to distract us.
slow us down.

44
00:02:44.699 --> 00:02:46.366
but he didn't know
that Will switched phones.

45
00:02:46.501 --> 00:02:48.036
Will could still be alive.

46
00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:49.302
That's good enough for me.

47
00:02:49.436 --> 00:02:50.838
Let's go find him.

48
00:02:50.972 --> 00:02:53.708
I'll tell the marshals
to keep the roadblocks up.

49
00:03:26.007 --> 00:03:28.241
Time to die.

50
00:03:39.620 --> 00:03:41.889
Now you get your keys.

51
00:03:44.324 --> 00:03:45.560
Watch out.

52
00:04:22.697 --> 00:04:26.466
Will. I can't feel my legs.

53
00:04:27.702 --> 00:04:29.369
You don't need them anymore.

54
00:04:29.504 --> 00:04:31.005
Come... Come on. Will.

55
00:04:31.539 --> 00:04:32.840
This isn't like you...

56
00:04:39.379 --> 00:04:41.849
<i>In 100 feet. turn right.</i>

57
00:04:43.316 --> 00:04:45.352
<i>Turn right.</i>

58
00:04:49.422 --> 00:04:51.291
<i>You have missed the turn.</i>

59
00:04:51.424 --> 00:04:52.960
<i>To reach GBI headquarters--</i>

60
00:04:53.094 --> 00:04:54.729
Eduardo. cancel directions.

61
00:04:54.862 --> 00:04:57.265
<i>Would you like to</i>
<i>set a new destination?</i>

62
00:05:00.400 --> 00:05:01.903
<i>Where are you going. Will?</i>

63
00:05:02.036 --> 00:05:04.205
<i>Where are you going. Will?</i>

64
00:05:04.639 --> 00:05:06.207
<i>Where are you going. Will?</i>

65
00:05:06.339 --> 00:05:08.109
I don't know. Eduardo.

66
00:05:09.243 --> 00:05:11.646
I've got the bad guy.
but I gotta tell you.

67
00:05:12.613 --> 00:05:14.314
I don't feel
like bringing him in.

68
00:05:14.447 --> 00:05:16.483
Hey. who you talking to?

69
00:05:16.617 --> 00:05:18.786
<i>It sounds </i>
<i>like you are taking</i>
<i>the law into your own hands.</i>

70
00:05:20.221 --> 00:05:21.454
Maybe.

71
00:05:22.824 --> 00:05:24.926
Maybe I'm not
done with him just yet.

72
00:05:25.059 --> 00:05:27.929
Will. I can't feel my leg.

73
00:05:28.062 --> 00:05:29.096
I'm clotting.

74
00:05:47.582 --> 00:05:48.916
Get any sleep?

75
00:05:49.482 --> 00:05:52.352
Good morning.
What can I do for you?

76
00:05:52.485 --> 00:05:54.555
Well. we have a problem.

77
00:05:54.689 --> 00:05:58.226
You assigned GBI man power
to a search that I already
passed off to the marshals.

78
00:05:58.358 --> 00:06:00.493
We're searching
for Special Agent
Will Trent now.

79
00:06:00.628 --> 00:06:02.429
Yeah. you don't
make that call. I do.

80
00:06:02.563 --> 00:06:04.632
We don't even
have ID on the bodies yet.

81
00:06:04.765 --> 00:06:06.767
I was at the scene.
I saw enough.

82
00:06:07.134 --> 00:06:09.136
And I made the call
because you were asleep.

83
00:06:09.270 --> 00:06:14.474
Amanda. this is chaos. okay?
Only one of us can
be in charge here.

84
00:06:16.143 --> 00:06:19.280
Oh. look.
I just ended my medical leave.

85
00:06:19.714 --> 00:06:21.015
Let's make it me.

86
00:06:21.148 --> 00:06:22.817
Wagner. stop.
I want you to listen to me.

87
00:06:22.950 --> 00:06:25.385
I get it. You think
I'm an empty suit.

88
00:06:25.519 --> 00:06:28.623
Well. I think
you're a fire-breathing
HR violation.

89
00:06:28.756 --> 00:06:30.324
but I don't wanna
see you hurt yourself.

90
00:06:30.457 --> 00:06:32.459
They're waiting for me in
the conference room. Bill.

91
00:06:32.593 --> 00:06:34.729
I'll have Caroline
box up your things.

92
00:06:35.796 --> 00:06:40.400
This is Darren Torrenson.
Roommate of fiancée
number three. Jackie Weggle.

93
00:06:40.534 --> 00:06:43.871
He went missing yesterday.
and he's most likely the dead
body in the driver's seat.

94
00:06:44.005 --> 00:06:45.907
Makes sense.
He's a good body
match for Ulster.

95
00:06:46.040 --> 00:06:49.377
Yup. and with
strong confidence.
this is the passenger.

96
00:06:49.510 --> 00:06:52.479
He worked in
an office a few blocks away
from Jackie Weggle's home.

97
00:06:52.613 --> 00:06:54.148
Didn't make it back
past his lunch break.

98
00:06:54.515 --> 00:06:56.884
Ulster targeted him
because he's wearing
the right suit.

99
00:06:57.018 --> 00:06:58.819
If Ulster staged all this.

100
00:06:58.953 --> 00:07:00.688
then it means.
he has a new plan
to leave the country.

101
00:07:00.821 --> 00:07:03.224
Caleb's team has a location
on Will's Porsche.

102
00:07:03.357 --> 00:07:05.293
-What?
-It was abandoned
at a gas station

103
00:07:05.425 --> 00:07:07.295
20 miles from here.
You're all getting
the address right now.

104
00:07:07.427 --> 00:07:09.330
- Be smart
with your resources.

105
00:07:09.462 --> 00:07:11.732
Don't double up on leads
and coordinate with Ormewood.

106
00:07:11.866 --> 00:07:13.734
He's at everyone's disposal.

107
00:07:23.811 --> 00:07:24.912
We have this backwards.

108
00:07:25.513 --> 00:07:28.916
The hair. the blood back here.
Will had Ulster in custody.

109
00:07:29.050 --> 00:07:32.019
Car's here. Phone's here.
Where the hell is he?

110
00:07:43.164 --> 00:07:45.498
He had over half a tank.
He didn't need gas.

111
00:07:45.967 --> 00:07:47.501
Any idea what his code is?

112
00:07:48.069 --> 00:07:50.404
Try 1323. Betty's gotcha date.

113
00:07:50.538 --> 00:07:52.740
0630. the address
of the group home.

114
00:07:52.873 --> 00:07:57.611
Uh... 7499? 1106? 1104?

115
00:07:57.745 --> 00:07:58.946
That's it.

116
00:07:59.647 --> 00:08:03.117
Stake an ex. Polaski.
That's our secret
weapon of finding him.

117
00:08:07.588 --> 00:08:09.223
I just saw the one dude.

118
00:08:09.357 --> 00:08:12.293
He was troubled.
stomping around.
yelling on the phone.

119
00:08:12.426 --> 00:08:14.395
-What was he yelling about?
-Wasn't my business.

120
00:08:14.528 --> 00:08:17.598
I closed our shop.
did inventory.
When I came back. he was gone.

121
00:08:17.732 --> 00:08:19.066
You never thought
to call the authorities?

122
00:08:19.200 --> 00:08:21.469
There's a methadone clinic
right up the road.

123
00:08:21.602 --> 00:08:24.839
I got crazies coming in here
all the time. I figured he
was one. and he'd be back.

124
00:08:24.972 --> 00:08:26.640
We're gonna need
your security footage.

125
00:08:26.774 --> 00:08:28.175
I just did a double.

126
00:08:28.809 --> 00:08:30.678
I'm out. Call my boss.

127
00:08:30.811 --> 00:08:33.948
Keep acting like a jackass.
you're gonna find out
how long a day can be.

128
00:08:34.715 --> 00:08:36.550
Don't look at me.
He's a sheriff.

129
00:08:36.684 --> 00:08:38.085
That badge means
he doesn't answer to anyone.

130
00:08:38.219 --> 00:08:40.721
He could impound your car.
throw you in jail.

131
00:08:40.855 --> 00:08:43.824
I was thinking more
like a very public
arrest for child pornography.

132
00:08:43.958 --> 00:08:46.527
Oh. Sure. Well.
that's a bold way to move.

133
00:08:46.660 --> 00:08:48.162
Okay. okay.

134
00:08:49.296 --> 00:08:50.531
God.

135
00:08:55.269 --> 00:08:56.904
There he is.

136
00:08:57.671 --> 00:08:58.773
<i>What are you doing. Will?</i>

137
00:08:58.906 --> 00:09:00.841
I'm not listening to you. okay?

138
00:09:00.975 --> 00:09:04.345
I actually pulled over
to get a new phone.
One that stays out of my head.

139
00:09:05.813 --> 00:09:07.314
You were right.
Will had Ulster.

140
00:09:07.448 --> 00:09:09.683
Where was he taking him?

141
00:09:09.817 --> 00:09:12.053
<i>I'd like to remind you</i>
<i>that you are a pathologically</i>
<i>scrupulous person.</i>

142
00:09:12.186 --> 00:09:14.088
Yeah. well. people can change.

143
00:09:14.622 --> 00:09:16.490
Right. I bring him in.
then what. huh?

144
00:09:16.624 --> 00:09:20.694
He escapes again.
More people die.
Whose fault is that?

145
00:09:20.828 --> 00:09:23.364
- <i>His.</i>
- Wrong. It's mine.

146
00:09:23.864 --> 00:09:26.767
He's a virus. a predator. okay?

147
00:09:27.134 --> 00:09:29.937
And he's not gonna stop.
but I can end this now.

148
00:09:30.071 --> 00:09:32.973
Will. whatever you're
thinking of doing. don't.

149
00:09:33.107 --> 00:09:35.476
Unlike me.
you have a conscience.

150
00:09:35.609 --> 00:09:37.278
No one's talking to you!

151
00:09:43.384 --> 00:09:45.586
Who's this lady now?

152
00:09:45.719 --> 00:09:47.721
<i>Would you like me</i>
<i>to begin a to-do list</i>
<i>for covering up a murder?</i>

153
00:09:47.855 --> 00:09:50.257
Oh. let's be clear.
it is not murder.

154
00:09:50.391 --> 00:09:54.295
If I kill James Ulster.
it is absolutely a form
of self-defense.

155
00:09:54.762 --> 00:09:56.063
-Oh!
-Oh.

156
00:09:56.797 --> 00:10:00.835
Uh... No need to worry. ma'am.
Just an official GBI matter.

157
00:10:01.268 --> 00:10:02.303
Help!

158
00:10:04.004 --> 00:10:07.408
I... I know
this all must look
and sound crazy.

159
00:10:07.542 --> 00:10:10.077
I'm actually transporting
a very dangerous criminal.

160
00:10:10.211 --> 00:10:12.613
- Hey. I need you to be quiet. all right?
-  -Help!

161
00:10:16.884 --> 00:10:18.520
Oh. my God.

162
00:10:18.686 --> 00:10:21.655
Hey. will you shut up?
You're scaring
this poor lady over here.

163
00:10:22.591 --> 00:10:24.391
Help!

164
00:10:30.164 --> 00:10:32.366
-Jesus. Will.
-Oh! Yikes.

165
00:10:33.834 --> 00:10:35.269
The hell?

166
00:10:35.402 --> 00:10:36.437
They know each other?

167
00:10:37.805 --> 00:10:41.842
You almost ruined everything!
How could you
let yourself get captured?

168
00:10:41.976 --> 00:10:45.913
Baby. it's fine.
No one knows we're here.

169
00:10:46.947 --> 00:10:48.249
The plan is still good.

170
00:10:55.289 --> 00:10:57.358
She never shows
her face to the camera.

171
00:10:57.491 --> 00:10:59.093
I can zoom in.

172
00:11:02.329 --> 00:11:03.831
Look out!

173
00:11:07.001 --> 00:11:10.671
We have no idea who she is.
and what she wants.

174
00:11:11.038 --> 00:11:12.706
They could be anywhere by now.

175
00:11:59.220 --> 00:12:02.423
-Hey. hey. hey. hey!
-Ow!

176
00:12:02.557 --> 00:12:04.258
Who's the woman. James?

177
00:12:05.793 --> 00:12:07.361
Her name is Susan.

178
00:12:07.494 --> 00:12:09.730
She is my loving fiancée.

179
00:12:13.267 --> 00:12:14.835
Where'd she take us. huh?

180
00:12:15.336 --> 00:12:19.406
She's taking me to the new
life of freedom
I richly deserve.

181
00:12:19.541 --> 00:12:23.877
Oh. yeah? Then why'd she put
a stun cuff on your leg. huh?

182
00:12:27.147 --> 00:12:29.383
I'm sure she
has some good reason.

183
00:12:30.184 --> 00:12:31.418
Let me handle this.

184
00:12:31.553 --> 00:12:33.954
I've got her
wrapped around my finger.

185
00:12:36.591 --> 00:12:38.627
Susan. my angel.

186
00:12:38.759 --> 00:12:40.494
I know about
the other women. Jimmy.

187
00:12:41.428 --> 00:12:42.664
They don't mean a thing.

188
00:12:42.796 --> 00:12:46.668
They were mere stepping stones
to our everlasting love.

189
00:12:46.800 --> 00:12:48.369
I'll explain
when we get to Canada.

190
00:12:48.503 --> 00:12:50.204
Canada is canceled.

191
00:12:50.337 --> 00:12:52.840
Wrapped around
your finger. huh?

192
00:12:54.341 --> 00:12:56.076
-We might have a problem.
-Mmm.

193
00:13:12.594 --> 00:13:16.363
If you'd just stayed
on the road and taken me
into the GBI.

194
00:13:16.497 --> 00:13:18.767
If you had just stayed
in prison to begin with.

195
00:13:29.778 --> 00:13:31.812
Hi. boys.

196
00:13:31.945 --> 00:13:35.482
I popped things off
on the lowest setting so we can
all agree on who's in charge.

197
00:13:35.617 --> 00:13:36.817
Anyone pee themselves?

198
00:13:36.950 --> 00:13:38.352
Yes? No?

199
00:13:39.654 --> 00:13:43.023
Hi. um. Ms. Susan.

200
00:13:43.157 --> 00:13:45.893
I'm Special Agent Will Trent
with the GBI. Um...

201
00:13:46.293 --> 00:13:49.363
Could the two of us
just have a one on one?

202
00:13:49.496 --> 00:13:50.565
Not interested.

203
00:13:51.031 --> 00:13:52.266
Back of the trailer.

204
00:13:53.033 --> 00:13:54.935
Come on.

205
00:14:00.775 --> 00:14:04.378
This little fellow goes to 11.
which will stop your heart.

206
00:14:04.512 --> 00:14:07.114
You've always been
in charge of my heart. my--

207
00:14:07.247 --> 00:14:09.883
Spare me the sugar-talk. Jimmy.

208
00:14:12.687 --> 00:14:15.356
Here. Clean yourselves up.

209
00:14:15.489 --> 00:14:17.424
Had to be
a dribble or two. huh?

210
00:14:17.559 --> 00:14:20.994
I'll be back in two shakes
of a dog's butt.

211
00:14:21.395 --> 00:14:22.429
Bzz.

212
00:14:23.063 --> 00:14:25.432
Just kidding. Got you.

213
00:14:39.880 --> 00:14:40.914
-Turn around.
-What?

214
00:14:41.048 --> 00:14:43.050
You turn around.

215
00:14:50.658 --> 00:14:52.459
So. Jimmy.

216
00:14:53.260 --> 00:14:54.596
What's your plan?

217
00:14:55.262 --> 00:14:58.232
When the door opens.
we rush her.

218
00:14:58.733 --> 00:14:59.834
You hold her down.

219
00:15:00.502 --> 00:15:03.404
I'll rip her throat out
with my teeth.

220
00:15:03.772 --> 00:15:04.706
I'm never doing that.

221
00:15:04.839 --> 00:15:06.106
Please. don't act all superior.

222
00:15:06.240 --> 00:15:07.474
You were gonna kill me.

223
00:15:08.275 --> 00:15:09.811
I should have kept my head.

224
00:15:09.943 --> 00:15:11.746
I'd be home
with my dog right now.

225
00:15:11.880 --> 00:15:15.082
I'm just saying.
a throat rip can
be a real problem-solver

226
00:15:15.215 --> 00:15:17.050
and your dog
isn't feeding itself.

227
00:15:17.184 --> 00:15:20.120
You know. I really do hope that
part of her plan
involves hurting you.

228
00:15:23.290 --> 00:15:25.527
So. it's to be
death by humiliation.

229
00:15:27.796 --> 00:15:30.097
Come on.

230
00:15:31.633 --> 00:15:33.200
Almost there.

231
00:15:34.502 --> 00:15:35.537
Go on.

232
00:15:35.670 --> 00:15:37.070
Hustle. come on.

233
00:15:42.644 --> 00:15:43.678
Go on.

234
00:15:48.783 --> 00:15:50.150
What the hell is this?

235
00:15:50.951 --> 00:15:52.252
Home.

236
00:15:53.253 --> 00:15:54.656
Have a seat.

237
00:16:06.233 --> 00:16:09.203
You don't expect me
to eat this?

238
00:16:09.336 --> 00:16:12.005
That is
a complete holiday meal.

239
00:16:12.139 --> 00:16:15.944
Turkey. turkey dressing.
veggie. tater cake.

240
00:16:16.076 --> 00:16:17.444
It's gray.

241
00:16:18.212 --> 00:16:20.080
It's... it's great.

242
00:16:20.214 --> 00:16:25.720
Um. and this.
this is a lovely room.

243
00:16:26.119 --> 00:16:27.387
It's very warm.

244
00:16:27.956 --> 00:16:30.625
Did you do all this yourself?

245
00:16:31.391 --> 00:16:32.426
Yes.

246
00:16:36.330 --> 00:16:38.332
That's... It's impressive.

247
00:16:38.465 --> 00:16:42.135
It's a space that you feel
like you can settle into.

248
00:16:42.804 --> 00:16:44.037
Thank you.

249
00:16:45.640 --> 00:16:48.041
- I love interior design.
- Mm.

250
00:16:48.175 --> 00:16:49.443
That's what I had in mind.

251
00:16:50.143 --> 00:16:53.515
-Oh.
-I'd be honored to say grace.

252
00:16:54.682 --> 00:16:56.183
If you'd like?

253
00:17:02.289 --> 00:17:04.057
Well. go on then.

254
00:17:05.927 --> 00:17:07.160
Jimmy.

255
00:17:14.201 --> 00:17:16.336
Bless us. O Lord.
and these thy gifts

256
00:17:16.470 --> 00:17:19.406
which we are about to receive
from thy bounty

257
00:17:19.541 --> 00:17:21.041
through Christ. our Lord.

258
00:17:21.174 --> 00:17:22.944
Yeah. hang on a second. bud.
Let me finish this search.

259
00:17:23.076 --> 00:17:25.178
<i>How come you can use AI</i>
<i>to look up license plates.</i>

260
00:17:25.312 --> 00:17:26.714
<i>but I can't use it</i>
<i>for my homework?</i>

261
00:17:26.848 --> 00:17:28.550
Well. let me know
when your homework is finding

262
00:17:28.683 --> 00:17:30.685
a kidnapped special agent.
and I'll make an exception.

263
00:17:32.854 --> 00:17:34.722
Hold on a second.

264
00:17:40.294 --> 00:17:41.696
<i>Hey. are you okay?</i>

265
00:17:45.567 --> 00:17:47.835
<i>You usually don't do work</i>
<i>the third day after chemo.</i>

266
00:17:48.670 --> 00:17:49.704
I'm good.

267
00:17:49.837 --> 00:17:51.973
<i>Daddy.</i>
<i>did you see Max's new perm?</i>

268
00:17:52.105 --> 00:17:53.473
His what? His perm?

269
00:17:53.608 --> 00:17:55.843
<i>All right. </i>
<i>t's a light perm.</i>

270
00:17:55.977 --> 00:17:58.412
<i>Guys are doing it now.</i>
<i>It's not that big of a deal.</i>

271
00:17:58.546 --> 00:17:59.714
Yeah.

272
00:17:59.847 --> 00:18:00.949
Okay.

273
00:18:01.081 --> 00:18:02.416
Yeah. it's...

274
00:18:03.851 --> 00:18:05.252
it's very boingy.

275
00:18:05.385 --> 00:18:07.889
I like you're trying things.

276
00:18:08.022 --> 00:18:11.291
Okay. Here. This is promising.

277
00:18:11.425 --> 00:18:13.661
Right. there's
our mysterious lady
in the sun hat.

278
00:18:13.795 --> 00:18:17.732
and we don't care
that we can't see
your face because we can see...

279
00:18:20.902 --> 00:18:23.170
There's no plate.
How can there be no plate?

280
00:18:25.405 --> 00:18:28.141
- <i>Sorry. Dad.</i>
-No. no. we don't give up.

281
00:18:28.275 --> 00:18:30.044
We... Aha!

282
00:18:30.177 --> 00:18:31.913
There. it's a sticker.

283
00:18:32.046 --> 00:18:34.716
It's an oil change sticker
and I know that place.

284
00:18:34.849 --> 00:18:36.985
They give discounts
to law enforcement.

285
00:18:37.117 --> 00:18:38.920
<i>You think she's a cop?</i>

286
00:18:39.053 --> 00:18:40.855
I think that they have
a location right next
to the state prison.

287
00:18:40.989 --> 00:18:43.825
I'd say there's a good chance
she's a correctional officer.

288
00:18:44.191 --> 00:18:47.762
<i>-All right. Dad. let's go.</i>
<i>-Go. Dad. Go. Dad. Go. go. go.</i>

289
00:18:47.895 --> 00:18:49.196
<i>Go. Dad.</i>

290
00:18:56.804 --> 00:18:58.673
May I say something?

291
00:18:59.306 --> 00:19:02.577
You were right.
That was delicious.

292
00:19:02.710 --> 00:19:05.780
- Mm. mm. mm!
- Mm-hmm!

293
00:19:05.913 --> 00:19:07.180
Mm!

294
00:19:07.314 --> 00:19:10.518
Family recipe.

295
00:19:11.218 --> 00:19:14.822
So. Ms. Susan.
how'd you two
lovebirds hit it off?

296
00:19:14.956 --> 00:19:17.491
I'm guessing you
were correctional officer?

297
00:19:17.925 --> 00:19:20.828
The way you've handled us
and your attention to detail.

298
00:19:20.962 --> 00:19:24.632
Well. started in tiny ways.

299
00:19:24.766 --> 00:19:30.004
That's how
the strongest love is built.
Slowly. over time.

300
00:19:30.505 --> 00:19:36.878
Little hellos on his way to
the prison library
and the secret notes.

301
00:19:38.846 --> 00:19:42.950
Who knew a life sentence
would bring a life partner?

302
00:19:46.054 --> 00:19:47.588
Hmm?

303
00:19:47.722 --> 00:19:50.490
Well. I'm sure the other women
felt as special as I did.

304
00:19:56.329 --> 00:20:03.037
But unlike them. we had
time together. stolen moments
that added up over years.

305
00:20:03.171 --> 00:20:08.910
What began
as a dalliance became.
ooh. undeniable.

306
00:20:09.744 --> 00:20:10.912
Oh!

307
00:20:13.147 --> 00:20:18.686
Ms. Susan. is it possible
that this entire situation

308
00:20:18.820 --> 00:20:21.589
is just all
a terrible misunderstanding?

309
00:20:21.723 --> 00:20:23.691
Well. I don't know
if I believe him.

310
00:20:23.825 --> 00:20:29.262
I'm highly specialized in
reading people and
interrogation. and his words.

311
00:20:29.931 --> 00:20:31.933
- they ring genuine to me.
- Mm.

312
00:20:33.266 --> 00:20:35.302
I love you.

313
00:20:38.706 --> 00:20:40.975
Why don't we play
roses and thorns?

314
00:20:42.110 --> 00:20:43.678
What's roses and thorns?

315
00:20:44.145 --> 00:20:47.414
We do it after every
dinner in my family.

316
00:20:47.548 --> 00:20:48.850
You'll catch on. okay?

317
00:20:48.983 --> 00:20:54.488
My rose is I finally
get to be with my Jimmy.

318
00:20:54.622 --> 00:20:57.457
away from everyone.
with just our love.

319
00:20:58.192 --> 00:21:02.563
And my thorn is having
to use the stun cuff on you.

320
00:21:03.131 --> 00:21:04.198
And you.

321
00:21:04.665 --> 00:21:06.500
Okay. how about you. Jimmy?

322
00:21:06.934 --> 00:21:09.036
What's your rose?
What's your thorn?

323
00:21:13.708 --> 00:21:15.408
Uh...

324
00:21:15.977 --> 00:21:18.546
I'm all thorns
right now. Suzie.

325
00:21:18.679 --> 00:21:23.785
I didn't spend a year planning
and risking my life
on a prison escape.

326
00:21:24.351 --> 00:21:27.855
only to be captured
by a menopausal harpy
with thick shoes.

327
00:21:27.989 --> 00:21:33.094
I can only think of one rose
and it is a fantasy

328
00:21:33.728 --> 00:21:35.730
of sewing your mouth shut.

329
00:21:37.832 --> 00:21:39.901
Oh. my.

330
00:21:42.270 --> 00:21:44.238
Just for that. no dessert.

331
00:21:50.111 --> 00:21:53.681
You can be so bossy
and demeaning.

332
00:21:53.815 --> 00:21:57.852
I want you to learn
that I deserve
more than just a lover.

333
00:21:57.985 --> 00:22:00.555
I deserve a partner.

334
00:22:03.191 --> 00:22:07.460
Figure it out.
Before you don't have
any more fingers to lose.

335
00:22:08.963 --> 00:22:10.430
Come here.

336
00:22:22.475 --> 00:22:23.711
Oh.

337
00:22:24.444 --> 00:22:25.680
All better.

338
00:22:26.981 --> 00:22:28.049
Okay.

339
00:22:31.418 --> 00:22:32.653
Get some rest.

340
00:22:34.889 --> 00:22:36.791
Momma's got
some errands to run.

341
00:22:36.924 --> 00:22:39.794
Just never ends
with taking care of you two.

342
00:22:47.768 --> 00:22:49.971
What do you think
about a throat rip now?

343
00:22:50.905 --> 00:22:55.943
I'm guessing the finger that
you had her wrapped around
is the one she cut off?

344
00:22:56.077 --> 00:22:58.246
Where did you learn
that dopey prayer?

345
00:22:58.378 --> 00:23:00.248
Foster care.

346
00:23:00.380 --> 00:23:03.517
It's also where I learned how
to keep a bad marriage
from getting me killed.

347
00:23:04.719 --> 00:23:06.187
What does that mean?

348
00:23:06.320 --> 00:23:07.822
She's out of range.

349
00:23:08.189 --> 00:23:10.091
I'm guessing it's 150 yards.

350
00:23:10.791 --> 00:23:12.927
Which puts her
outside the building.

351
00:23:16.864 --> 00:23:19.600
-Oh!
-I'm getting this
condenser out.

352
00:23:20.234 --> 00:23:23.704
-Then we crawl through--
-You little scamp.

353
00:23:25.106 --> 00:23:26.941
Don't give me nicknames.

354
00:23:28.408 --> 00:23:30.912
Okay. Okay. here's
the employee list
from the warden.

355
00:23:31.045 --> 00:23:35.016
- It's 400 names.
123 of them are female.

356
00:23:35.650 --> 00:23:37.351
We can narrow it down. Ow.

357
00:23:37.484 --> 00:23:39.253
You good?

358
00:23:39.387 --> 00:23:41.522
Ah. it's just a cramp.
I'm not drinking enough water.

359
00:23:41.656 --> 00:23:44.125
Hey. how many
of them drive pickup trucks?

360
00:23:44.258 --> 00:23:45.458
Can you figure that out?

361
00:23:45.593 --> 00:23:47.595
Watch how my fingers fly.

362
00:23:48.729 --> 00:23:52.166
Watching you type is like
watching a dog dance
on its hind legs.

363
00:23:52.900 --> 00:23:56.570
Thank you.
And we are down to 23 women.

364
00:23:56.704 --> 00:23:58.272
You know. 23 is manageable.

365
00:23:58.406 --> 00:23:59.907
Okay.
let me get this list
to Faith and Caleb

366
00:24:00.041 --> 00:24:01.842
then we
can coordinate interviews.

367
00:24:02.243 --> 00:24:03.544
You ready. Polaski?

368
00:24:08.549 --> 00:24:10.584
Just... give me a sec.

369
00:24:10.718 --> 00:24:12.485
You know what else
feels like a cramp?

370
00:24:12.620 --> 00:24:13.921
A contraction.

371
00:24:14.055 --> 00:24:15.790
What. you want me
to get it checked out?

372
00:24:18.392 --> 00:24:20.528
Fine. I'll get it checked out.
It's nothing.

373
00:24:20.962 --> 00:24:22.730
-You want me to come with?
-No. no.

374
00:24:23.264 --> 00:24:26.100
Keep looking for sun hat lady
and keep me posted.

375
00:24:31.305 --> 00:24:32.406
One more.

376
00:24:33.240 --> 00:24:35.443
Look. when I get back.
I'm gonna tell you
a story about the time

377
00:24:35.576 --> 00:24:38.212
that me and this guy
were working
a prison transport.

378
00:24:38.346 --> 00:24:40.381
Some idiot tried to carjack us.

379
00:24:40.848 --> 00:24:43.150
- Can't wait.
- I'll be right back.

380
00:24:46.020 --> 00:24:47.888
You said this guy
could be a shortcut?

381
00:24:48.022 --> 00:24:49.156
He's my contact.

382
00:24:49.290 --> 00:24:50.658
Let me play him.

383
00:24:54.662 --> 00:24:56.530
I can't believe
Will didn't call me.

384
00:24:57.131 --> 00:25:01.802
Yeah. I'm sure that he feels
completely responsible
for Calvin.

385
00:25:04.839 --> 00:25:09.810
Look. He takes a long time
to open up to someone.

386
00:25:10.244 --> 00:25:13.047
I'm sure what he went through
in his childhood didn't help.

387
00:25:15.783 --> 00:25:18.686
So. you said kidnapping
with two victims. huh?

388
00:25:19.053 --> 00:25:20.855
That made me think.
a couple of weeks back.

389
00:25:20.988 --> 00:25:23.691
a pair of stun cuffs went
missing with the remote.

390
00:25:24.058 --> 00:25:26.093
That's like ten grand in value.

391
00:25:26.227 --> 00:25:28.896
Warden couldn't figure it out.
swept the whole thing
under the rug.

392
00:25:29.397 --> 00:25:30.698
That's all I can tell you.

393
00:25:32.733 --> 00:25:34.635
We have a list of names.

394
00:25:34.769 --> 00:25:37.671
Maybe you could take a look
at it and see if anyone
makes sense for this.

395
00:25:45.679 --> 00:25:48.582
Hmm. Well.
this one here. I know her.

396
00:25:49.016 --> 00:25:51.118
She would have had access.

397
00:25:53.754 --> 00:25:55.089
Susan Barno.

398
00:26:04.498 --> 00:26:06.300
Hmm.

399
00:26:06.901 --> 00:26:08.936
She is absolutely fine.

400
00:26:09.070 --> 00:26:10.838
Those are
Braxton-Hicks contractions.

401
00:26:10.971 --> 00:26:12.940
Perfectly normal
in the second
and third trimester.

402
00:26:13.074 --> 00:26:14.543
The third too? That's good.

403
00:26:14.675 --> 00:26:15.943
Something to look forward to.

404
00:26:16.077 --> 00:26:17.912
Well. there's also.
you know. the baby.

405
00:26:18.045 --> 00:26:19.947
- Right.
- Stay hydrated.

406
00:26:20.081 --> 00:26:22.283
Try shifting positions
or walking around
if they get too uncomfortable.

407
00:26:22.416 --> 00:26:24.051
Okay. Thanks.

408
00:26:24.519 --> 00:26:25.520
-Thank you.
-Yep.

409
00:26:25.653 --> 00:26:26.954
It's a relief.

410
00:26:27.088 --> 00:26:29.156
-Yeah. Yeah.
-Can you check that for me?

411
00:26:30.591 --> 00:26:32.259
It's 7834.

412
00:26:33.294 --> 00:26:34.361
Phone code?

413
00:26:34.495 --> 00:26:37.098
-What a gesture of intimacy.
-Is it work?

414
00:26:38.399 --> 00:26:39.700
Why. are you working?

415
00:26:39.834 --> 00:26:42.336
You know
I can't sit this one out.

416
00:26:44.071 --> 00:26:46.674
Hey. how about I...
how about I pick up a pizza...

417
00:26:46.807 --> 00:26:48.976
-Barno's? Barno's?
-...on the way home.
Detroit style.

418
00:26:49.110 --> 00:26:51.879
- Hell yeah. Barno's.
I feel like.
- Yeah? Good.

419
00:26:52.012 --> 00:26:54.014
You remember
Barno's packaged foods?

420
00:26:54.148 --> 00:26:57.818
I feel like they had
a big warehouse
in. like. Dunwoody.

421
00:26:57.952 --> 00:27:00.154
What the hell
are you doing. Angie?

422
00:27:01.222 --> 00:27:02.823
We are trying to find Will.

423
00:27:02.957 --> 00:27:04.992
He doesn't need you right now.
Our baby needs you.

424
00:27:05.527 --> 00:27:07.928
Okay. feel free to keep
telling me what I can
and cannot do.

425
00:27:08.062 --> 00:27:09.830
No. I'm telling you
what you should do.

426
00:27:09.964 --> 00:27:11.866
You should rest.
You should stay hydrated.

427
00:27:11.999 --> 00:27:14.603
APB. GBI. marshals. sheriffs.

428
00:27:14.735 --> 00:27:18.172
everybody with
a badge in Atlanta
is out there looking for him.

429
00:27:23.043 --> 00:27:24.879
Wish I could be like you.

430
00:27:25.580 --> 00:27:27.114
-Okay.
-No. no. listen.

431
00:27:27.248 --> 00:27:30.284
Really. I wish
I had grown up just...

432
00:27:31.652 --> 00:27:33.721
living my life.

433
00:27:35.723 --> 00:27:37.324
No constant fear.

434
00:27:38.726 --> 00:27:40.828
No wondering if...

435
00:27:42.196 --> 00:27:46.800
anyone is going
to come and save you.

436
00:27:49.538 --> 00:27:50.771
Will has come.

437
00:27:50.905 --> 00:27:52.239
He's always come.

438
00:27:52.373 --> 00:27:54.108
He has saved me...

439
00:27:55.610 --> 00:27:59.246
over and over.

440
00:28:00.649 --> 00:28:02.116
He's my family.

441
00:28:05.152 --> 00:28:07.188
You're right. You're right.

442
00:28:07.321 --> 00:28:09.924
I grew up feeling safe.

443
00:28:11.593 --> 00:28:13.928
It's not wrong
to want that for my child.

444
00:28:14.862 --> 00:28:18.199
This is your family.
I'm your family.

445
00:28:22.436 --> 00:28:23.837
I'll see you at home.

446
00:28:30.244 --> 00:28:31.378
Okay.

447
00:28:33.214 --> 00:28:35.115
Isn't it funny how
we ended up like this.

448
00:28:35.249 --> 00:28:39.954
Classic father-son bonding.
using tools and our muscles.

449
00:28:40.087 --> 00:28:42.890
We are not bonding. okay?
And you are not my father.

450
00:28:43.023 --> 00:28:44.458
Well. almost was.

451
00:28:45.059 --> 00:28:47.294
Your mother and I
were very close.

452
00:28:47.662 --> 00:28:48.896
When Lucy started...

453
00:28:49.330 --> 00:28:51.398
-Hey! Whoa!
-I can't.

454
00:28:57.137 --> 00:28:59.507
-Damn it!
-We have to switch places.

455
00:28:59.641 --> 00:29:01.909
You have nine fingers.
What are you gonna do?

456
00:29:02.042 --> 00:29:03.911
-I can't hold you.
-No way I'm letting you

457
00:29:04.044 --> 00:29:05.779
-hold anything sharp.
-We have to switch places.

458
00:29:05.913 --> 00:29:07.181
Can't get leverage
on the last thing.

459
00:29:07.314 --> 00:29:08.516
-We need a new angle.
-How do we get...

460
00:29:08.650 --> 00:29:10.251
Hey. What are we gonna do?

461
00:29:10.851 --> 00:29:13.220
I don't know. okay?

462
00:29:15.657 --> 00:29:17.925
Don't lose your head.

463
00:29:18.959 --> 00:29:21.095
I'm not dying here with you.

464
00:29:24.599 --> 00:29:26.000
Oh. God!

465
00:29:29.770 --> 00:29:31.405
You deserve better.

466
00:29:35.843 --> 00:29:37.278
What was that?

467
00:29:37.746 --> 00:29:39.079
Is that an apology?

468
00:29:39.213 --> 00:29:43.250
No. no. An observation.

469
00:29:43.384 --> 00:29:44.852
A feeling.

470
00:29:44.985 --> 00:29:46.387
You...

471
00:29:47.821 --> 00:29:50.190
You're brilliant. loyal.

472
00:29:50.324 --> 00:29:51.559
You don't stop.

473
00:29:51.693 --> 00:29:53.294
I admire you.

474
00:29:55.462 --> 00:29:56.797
I love you.

475
00:29:57.666 --> 00:29:59.099
Oh. God.

476
00:29:59.233 --> 00:30:03.370
I hated you. I hated you for...
for taking Lucy away.

477
00:30:06.440 --> 00:30:09.209
I see her in you.

478
00:30:11.178 --> 00:30:12.913
But she had balance.

479
00:30:14.848 --> 00:30:16.817
You run from the dark.

480
00:30:18.118 --> 00:30:20.321
That's why it chases you.

481
00:30:28.062 --> 00:30:30.898
You ever regret
what you did to my mother?

482
00:30:33.334 --> 00:30:34.868
Yes.

483
00:30:41.308 --> 00:30:42.943
I was gonna kill you.

484
00:30:43.310 --> 00:30:49.216
Oh. so there is a monster
in there after all. Yeah.

485
00:30:53.020 --> 00:30:54.556
What are you doing?

486
00:30:55.022 --> 00:30:56.457
No. no. no.

487
00:30:57.525 --> 00:30:59.026
Hey. hey. hey.

488
00:30:59.159 --> 00:31:01.161
Easy. easy.

489
00:31:05.866 --> 00:31:07.569
What are you doing? Hey.

490
00:31:09.036 --> 00:31:11.372
What are you doing?
Stop. stop. stop.

491
00:31:11.506 --> 00:31:13.708
We're gonna tip
this bastard over

492
00:31:13.842 --> 00:31:17.111
because you're not gonna be
the last person to ever say
anything nice to me.

493
00:31:17.679 --> 00:31:19.947
Now get up! Let's go!

494
00:31:22.817 --> 00:31:25.886
One. two. three.

495
00:31:30.124 --> 00:31:31.358
Again. go.

496
00:31:34.161 --> 00:31:36.765
He's here. Ormewood.
I can feel it.

497
00:31:36.897 --> 00:31:39.967
<i>Caleb and Faith</i> <i>are ten minutes</i> <i>out.
 SWAT's right behind them.</i>

498
00:31:40.568 --> 00:31:43.070
All right. I'm gonna
keep an eye out.

499
00:31:43.505 --> 00:31:44.905
<i>Don't do anything stupid.</i>

500
00:31:45.038 --> 00:31:46.373
<i>-I'm serious.</i>
-Yep.

501
00:31:52.446 --> 00:31:54.314
I've told you about Will.

502
00:31:56.917 --> 00:31:58.419
He needs to meet you.

503
00:31:59.453 --> 00:32:01.121
We know what we're doing.

504
00:32:17.337 --> 00:32:18.506
Come on.

505
00:32:20.875 --> 00:32:22.376
She's back. We have to stop.

506
00:32:24.813 --> 00:32:26.213
No. We're doing this. Let's go.

507
00:33:29.811 --> 00:33:32.179
Enough of this misbehaving.

508
00:33:34.147 --> 00:33:37.384
Who's gonna put that
trailer right side up
again. huh?

509
00:33:42.055 --> 00:33:43.357
You.

510
00:33:43.725 --> 00:33:45.125
You're the bad apple.

511
00:33:45.259 --> 00:33:50.097
My Jimmy is a genius
in many ways
but he's not mechanical.

512
00:33:52.332 --> 00:33:54.736
-Will.
-Angie. get out of here.

513
00:33:55.670 --> 00:33:57.204
No!

514
00:34:01.174 --> 00:34:02.510
Who the hell is Angie?

515
00:34:03.143 --> 00:34:06.614
I swear to God. Jimmy.
if she's got your ring
on her finger...

516
00:34:08.148 --> 00:34:11.418
There is a limit
to what I will take.

517
00:34:19.226 --> 00:34:21.328
Angie. where are you?

518
00:34:28.135 --> 00:34:29.369
Damn it.

519
00:34:33.407 --> 00:34:37.110
You brought
such calamity upon our family.

520
00:34:37.244 --> 00:34:38.412
No!

521
00:34:38.546 --> 00:34:40.582
No!

522
00:34:47.187 --> 00:34:50.090
Oh. no. Jimmy!

523
00:34:50.223 --> 00:34:53.728
Oh. God. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

524
00:34:53.861 --> 00:34:57.230
No!

525
00:35:15.215 --> 00:35:17.417
-Police.
-Police. Get on the ground.

526
00:35:17.552 --> 00:35:20.120
- Drop your weapon.
- Get on the ground.

527
00:35:25.059 --> 00:35:26.326
I got cover.

528
00:35:39.741 --> 00:35:40.842
See you soon.

529
00:35:48.883 --> 00:35:50.317
Will.

530
00:36:06.701 --> 00:36:07.769
Hi.

531
00:36:08.936 --> 00:36:10.170
Did I wake you?

532
00:36:13.107 --> 00:36:14.575
Yesterday scared me. Angie.

533
00:36:15.143 --> 00:36:16.744
I mean. it really scared me.

534
00:36:16.878 --> 00:36:18.079
I know.

535
00:36:18.211 --> 00:36:20.014
Do you? I'm not...

536
00:36:20.148 --> 00:36:21.716
I'm not challenging you.

537
00:36:22.784 --> 00:36:24.519
I just wonder
if you understand.

538
00:36:32.727 --> 00:36:33.561
Tell me.

539
00:36:34.361 --> 00:36:37.632
I've never been held captive
by a deranged serial killer.

540
00:36:37.765 --> 00:36:40.068
Well.
it's a pretty exclusive club.

541
00:36:40.635 --> 00:36:42.970
But I do know what it's
like to lose the woman I love.

542
00:36:44.939 --> 00:36:45.973
Permanent loss.

543
00:36:47.141 --> 00:36:48.375
Also a crappy club.

544
00:36:48.776 --> 00:36:52.080
-We gotta join better clubs.
-Mm.

545
00:36:52.880 --> 00:36:56.450
I do get it.
I'm walking into a job
where anything can happen.

546
00:36:58.052 --> 00:36:59.120
Every day.

547
00:37:00.487 --> 00:37:04.726
-That's just the job.
-And you do it fearlessly.
It's so hot.

548
00:37:05.258 --> 00:37:08.129
But now it's not just you
heading into the danger.

549
00:37:08.261 --> 00:37:11.666
I think my womb might be
the safest place in Atlanta.

550
00:37:12.332 --> 00:37:14.001
I'm like a baby panic room.

551
00:37:18.472 --> 00:37:22.777
Life has been
on my back since I was five.

552
00:37:24.045 --> 00:37:26.647
It's tried a thousand ways
to take me down.

553
00:37:28.482 --> 00:37:29.817
I'm still standing.

554
00:37:32.053 --> 00:37:33.721
Can you trust me?

555
00:37:36.323 --> 00:37:38.291
You trust me
to take care of her?

556
00:37:39.060 --> 00:37:41.428
That's what this
stage of love is. I guess.

557
00:37:43.330 --> 00:37:46.134
Not a lot of songs about
the pain in the ass parts
of a relationship.

558
00:37:46.266 --> 00:37:49.036
-The baby-making part.
so many songs.
-So many songs.

559
00:37:49.170 --> 00:37:50.171
Yeah.

560
00:37:53.241 --> 00:37:58.345
I think. though.
that this stuff
is what really matters.

561
00:37:59.379 --> 00:38:00.615
Yeah.

562
00:38:03.951 --> 00:38:07.855
And dot. Okay.
let's see if I get this right.

563
00:38:09.257 --> 00:38:10.992
Just a dot. no L.

564
00:38:11.125 --> 00:38:12.459
Wow. guys.

565
00:38:12.593 --> 00:38:13.828
We should get
you two to make all the meals.

566
00:38:13.961 --> 00:38:16.463
Yeah. I'd settle
for kitchen clean-up.

567
00:38:16.597 --> 00:38:18.866
Well. I put in the blueberries
and the chocolate chips.

568
00:38:19.000 --> 00:38:20.601
Nice. Whoa!

569
00:38:20.735 --> 00:38:22.270
Those things don't really
go together. but...

570
00:38:22.402 --> 00:38:24.071
Yes. they do.

571
00:38:24.205 --> 00:38:27.074
- No. they don't.
- Hi. Hey. uh.
where are we today?

572
00:38:28.009 --> 00:38:29.110
About a three.

573
00:38:29.610 --> 00:38:31.179
You wanna go?

574
00:38:31.311 --> 00:38:33.014
I'll cover for you
and put them
in some Tupperware.

575
00:38:33.514 --> 00:38:35.983
-I'm okay. Thank you.
-Okay.

576
00:38:36.818 --> 00:38:38.485
So. how do you like it. Daddy?

577
00:38:38.619 --> 00:38:41.656
Mm! It's delicious. baby.

578
00:38:41.789 --> 00:38:44.091
How much longer
are you on desk duty?

579
00:38:44.225 --> 00:38:45.993
Couple more weeks. I hope.

580
00:38:46.127 --> 00:38:49.396
I mean. don't get me wrong.
I am an unexpected
computer genius.

581
00:38:50.097 --> 00:38:51.866
but my best work
is not behind a desk.

582
00:38:51.999 --> 00:38:53.734
We're going
with genius. are we?

583
00:38:53.868 --> 00:38:56.436
It's just... It's been nice
to FaceTime you during the day.

584
00:38:57.004 --> 00:38:59.674
Yeah. and you come home
a lot more when
you say you will.

585
00:39:00.340 --> 00:39:01.576
Oh.

586
00:39:03.177 --> 00:39:05.813
Well. those sound
like easy things
to keep going

587
00:39:05.947 --> 00:39:08.448
once your dad is
back in the field. right?

588
00:39:09.851 --> 00:39:11.018
Yeah.

589
00:39:14.387 --> 00:39:16.257
So. who has the syrup?

590
00:39:16.389 --> 00:39:18.159
-Ah. Here.
-Thank ya.

591
00:39:18.292 --> 00:39:20.995
-So. when can I drink coffee?
-I hear you like it black.
yeah?

592
00:39:21.394 --> 00:39:24.031
No. I'm kidding. I'm kidding.
You're not gonna want it.

593
00:39:29.770 --> 00:39:33.341
Amanda.
glad to hear
your golden boy is safe.

594
00:39:33.473 --> 00:39:34.474
How's he doing?

595
00:39:34.609 --> 00:39:36.577
He's been through worse.

596
00:39:37.612 --> 00:39:38.880
You forget
something in my office?

597
00:39:39.013 --> 00:39:41.115
Yeah. I spoke to
the director this morning.

598
00:39:41.249 --> 00:39:43.551
We had a good mind meld
about great leaders

599
00:39:43.684 --> 00:39:46.419
who couldn't see
when their time was done.

600
00:39:47.221 --> 00:39:48.322
Interesting.

601
00:39:48.990 --> 00:39:51.792
Our conversations are
usually about unqualified men

602
00:39:51.926 --> 00:39:54.528
pushing themselves into spaces
where they don't belong.

603
00:39:55.329 --> 00:39:58.966
You know there's no shame
in the next chapter. Amanda.

604
00:39:59.867 --> 00:40:01.836
Are you looking
for a fight. Bill?

605
00:40:02.303 --> 00:40:03.571
You'll get one.

606
00:40:09.911 --> 00:40:12.013
I hope this isn't
a wellness check.

607
00:40:13.314 --> 00:40:14.849
Just dropping in on family.

608
00:40:16.416 --> 00:40:17.785
How's Calvin?

609
00:40:18.920 --> 00:40:19.954
He's fine.

610
00:40:21.088 --> 00:40:22.189
How about you?

611
00:40:23.524 --> 00:40:26.459
Well. seeing
my therapist tomorrow.

612
00:40:27.628 --> 00:40:29.130
Dr. Roach.

613
00:40:29.597 --> 00:40:32.366
She has a whole plan for us.

614
00:40:32.499 --> 00:40:35.536
-Wants me to try Frisbee golf.
-Oh!

615
00:40:36.170 --> 00:40:38.673
Sounds helpful.

616
00:40:38.806 --> 00:40:42.843
Yeah. She's peculiar.
Frisbee golf.

617
00:40:43.277 --> 00:40:45.212
I mean. why are
we mashing those together?

618
00:40:45.346 --> 00:40:46.747
Keep it simple.

619
00:40:46.881 --> 00:40:48.015
Exactly.

620
00:40:50.985 --> 00:40:55.056
We found your car headed in
the opposite direction of GBI.

621
00:41:01.062 --> 00:41:04.265
I missed a turn and got lost.

622
00:41:05.366 --> 00:41:10.137
Unfamiliar terrain
and dyslexia. It's a bad
combination.

623
00:41:17.411 --> 00:41:20.548
Listen.
I don't wanna
force a conversation.

624
00:41:21.148 --> 00:41:23.884
but I want you to know
you can call me anytime.

625
00:41:24.685 --> 00:41:26.253
For anything.

626
00:41:27.521 --> 00:41:29.023
Hmm.

627
00:41:30.725 --> 00:41:33.094
I hope it brings you
relief that he's gone.

628
00:41:41.702 --> 00:41:43.504
The world is a safer place.

629
00:41:48.309 --> 00:41:50.945
I was gonna
make some café con leche.

630
00:41:52.013 --> 00:41:53.481
It takes me a few minutes.

631
00:41:56.417 --> 00:41:57.818
You want one?

632
00:41:58.252 --> 00:41:59.587
Yeah.

633
00:42:00.388 --> 00:42:01.989
I've got all day.

634
00:42:02.390 --> 00:42:03.791
All day?

635
00:42:03.924 --> 00:42:06.093
You got somebody better
you want to sit around with?

636
00:42:09.163 --> 00:42:10.297
I suppose not.

636
